<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1894-08-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1894-08-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="324" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d324">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Baker</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Managua</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1894-08-30"><hi rend="italic">August 30,
                            1894</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Tour cable has been received. I presented your demand promptly. The United
                        States citizens have been already expelled from Nicaragua without charges or
                        without trial. In spite of my protest Americans marked for arbitrary
                        expulsion. Awaiting your instructions.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>